values: 串；一系列；一排；一组；（一连串相关的事物中的）一部分；线；弦；筋；纤维；细绳；带子；（管弦乐团的）弦乐器；[物理学]弦理论中的基本对象；[计算机]字符串
系；排列；用线串；使成串；使成行；悬挂；扎；连接；把…连在一起；装上弦（如乐器）；拉紧琴弦；去除（豆荚等的）筋

synonym.mean: 扎，缚；使排成一列，串起；伸展，拉直

pos_mean_info_list.mean: 纵梁，纵桁；上弦匠；[地质] 细脉；特约记者，特约通讯员；拉线人

word_mean_info__list.difference: 指用于捆绑大物件的粗壮而坚固的绳子，一般用绵、毛、麻、金属或其它材料制成。
普通用词，指用棉、毛、丝或纤维等纹成的很细的线，通常用于缝纫、纺织等。
普通用词，指捆绑小件物品的细绳或细带子。
普通用词，含义广泛，指任何一种线，常作引申用。
指比string粗，比rope细，较牢固，通常用于捆扎较小物品的线或绳。用作引申当约束讲。

替补资源；替补方案；备选队员；二线队员

bilingual.source: He wrote a long string of zeros on the paper.
bilingual.target: 他在纸上写了一长串的零。

bilingual.source: The ciphertext appeared as a random string of characters.
bilingual.target: 密文看起来像一串随机字符。

bilingual.source: She is wearing a string of glittering and translucent pearls.
bilingual.target: 她戴着一串晶莹的珍珠项链。

bilingual.source: He hung a string of lights on the fence.
bilingual.target: 他在栅栏上挂了一串灯。

bilingual.source: Each char in the string has a unique index.
bilingual.target: 字符串中的每个字符都有一个唯一的索引。

bilingual.source: We made a colorful string of beads together.
bilingual.target: 我们一起做了一条五颜六色的串珠。

bilingual.source: The serial number is an alphanumeric string.
bilingual.target: 序列号是一个字母数字的字符串。

bilingual.source: This string of beads bracelet is made by me.
bilingual.target: 这个串珠手链是我自己做的。

bilingual.source: The string contains both letters and numbers.
bilingual.target: 这个字符串包含字母和数字。

bilingual.source: She wore a beautiful string of beads necklace.
bilingual.target: 她戴了一条漂亮的串珠项链。

list.abstract: C++、java、VB等编程语言中的字符串。 在java、C#中，String类是不可变的，对String类的任何改变，都是返回一个新的String类对象。 String 对象是System.Char对象的有序集合，用于表示字符串。String 对象的值是该有序集合的内容，并且该值是不可变的。
string，英语单词，名词，意为“ 线，弦，细绳；一串，一行”。

yingyinNormal.en: He gave her a string of pearls worth $350,000. But the morning of the wedding, Daisy received a letter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 给了她一串价值三十五万美元的珍珠，但婚礼当天上午黛西收到了一封信。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa has found some sticks. George has found some string.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩奇找到了两根棍子。乔治找到了一团绳子。

yingyinNormal.en: Step three: Remove string from bag, releasing the winds. Check.
yingyinNormal.zh: 第三步，把绳子解开，把风放出来。好的。

yingyinNormal.en: I know, we'll tie the string to your wrist, George. What a good idea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我知道了。我们可以把绳子系在乔治的腰上。好主意。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, a string quartet for the procession. A jazz trio for cocktails.
yingyinNormal.zh: 行进时用弦乐四重奏，鸡尾酒会时安排爵士乐。

yingyinNormal.en: Have you got a banjo? Four or five-string. You won't have a tree in your van?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的火车里有班卓琴吗。四弦还是五弦。你的货车里肯定没有树对不对。

yingyinNormal.en: Currently, you're being paid under a grant to specifically research string theory.
yingyinNormal.zh: 目前大学给你的研究基金是只能做特定领域研究的。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm the magic Fairy Carrot. Look, children. I can fly. There's a string lifting her up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是胡萝卜茉魔力仙女，我可以飞啊。那是他用一根绳子吊起来的。

yingyinNormal.en: Have you got a banjo? Four or five string? You won't have a tree in your van? Apple or pear?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的火车里有班卓琴吗？四弦还是五弦？你的货车里肯定没有树对不对？苹果树还是梨树？

yingyinNormal.en: You know, there's a foundational idea in string theory that the whole universe may be a hologram.
yingyinNormal.zh: 弦理论中，有个基本概念，宇宙可能是一张全息图。

yingyinNormal.en: Used to be string theory, now it's dark matter. But let's not discuss Sheldon. Let's get back to you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 之前是弦理论，现在换成了暗物质，不过我们还是不要谈谢尔顿了，还是来谈谈你吧。

yingyinNormal.en: I assume you'd like to reopen our dialogue about the university forcing me to continue with string theory?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想你想要再开始大学逼我继续研究弦理论的谈话是吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Senior theoretical particle physicist at CalTech, focusing on M theory, or, in layman's terms, string theory.
yingyinNormal.zh: 加州理工学院的高级理论粒子物理学家，主要致力于M理论研究，外行人说法是弦理论。

yingyinNormal.en: But if I'm able to detect slow-moving magnetic monopoles there, I will be the scientis to confirm string theory.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但如果我能在北极勘测出慢速磁单极子，我就能成为证明弦理论的科学家。

yingyinNormal.en: So, I'm glad I ran into you. The Physics Department string quartet needs a new cellist. What happened to Elliot Wong?
yingyinNormal.zh: 碰见你太好了，物理系弦乐四重奏还缺一个大提琴。埃利奥特·王怎么啦？

yingyinNormal.en: Well, actually, the risk of throat cutting is very low. On the other hand, severe string burn is a real and ever-present danger.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实，割到喉咙的风险很低，另外，严重被线擦伤才是真实且经常发生的危险。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I'm working on time-dependent backgrounds in string theory, specifically quantum field theory in "d-dimensional" de Sitter space.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在研究弦理论的时间依赖性，尤其是量子场论在德西特时空d维空间中的应用。

yingyinNormal.en: I am the king of the castle. Every castle needs a telephone. Hold this. Keep this string nice and tight and you can talk to the boys.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是城堡的国王，每一个城堡都需要一个电话。拿着这个。接下来你们拿紧着绳子，就可以跟男孩们说话了。

yingyinNormal.en: What do you need that kind of money for? I have figured out an experimental design that may corroborate my latest thinking on string theory.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你要这么大一笔钱干什么啊？我想出了一个实验设计可以证实我最新的弦理论想法。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, that seems simple enough. Point bag away from home, feet firmly on ground, pull string, releasing the winds. All right, let's do it for real.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看上去很简单吗。把袋子指向家的反方向，站稳了，拉绳子把风放出来。好的，来做一遍吧。

sense_info_list.en: a sequentially ordered set of things or events or ideas

examination_example.sentence: When younger kids learn computer science, they learn that it's not just a confusing, endless <highlight>string</highlight> of letters and numbers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当更小的孩子学习计算机科学时，他们会发现它不仅仅是一串令人困惑的、无穷无尽的字母和数字。

examination_example.sentence: As a News Feature article in Nature discusses, a <highlight>string</highlight> of lucrative awards for researchers have joined the Nobel Prizes in recent years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正如《自然》杂志的一篇新闻专题文章所讨论的那样，近年来，一系列对研究人员有利可图的奖项加入了诺贝尔奖。

examination_example.sentence: A <highlight>string</highlight> of accidents raised serious questions about both Vermont Yankee's safety and Entergy's management.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一连串的事故对佛蒙特州扬基的安全和Entergy的管理提出了严重的问题。

word_usage.usage: string作名词，表示“一串；一系列”时，常用搭配是a string of sth.。
string作动词时，既可作及物动词，又可作不及物动词。作及物动词时，其后可直接接名词或者代词，如：string the shells on a silver chain 把贝壳串在银链上。
